criteria.textblock:
        Inclusion Criteria:

          1. HBsAg positive, HBeAg negative, antibody to HBeAg-positive;

          2. Stable administration of anti-HBV neucleos(t)ides analogue mono therapy for at least
             more than one and a half year;

          3. Demonstration of undetectable HBV DNA on three occasions, each at least 6 months
             apart, which is consistent with the APASL stopping rule;

          4. Patients read, understand the consent form, and signed the study consent.

        Exclusion Criteria:

          1. Patient with other liver diseases;

          2. Patient with concurrent hepatitis viruses or HIV infection;

          3. Patients are reluctant to stop their anti-HBV treatment.
